  "texts": [
    "For the effect of motivation on score improvements, a strong correlation was observed in the control group, with a Multiple R of 0.842 and an R-Square value of 70.1%, indicating that motivation accounted for a significant proportion of the variance in score improvements.",
    "However, the correlation was even stronger for the feedback group, where motivation accounted for an additional 10% of the variance in score differentials compared to the control group.",
    "This suggests that the feedback group benefited more from the motivational effects of the revision process.",
    "When examining the effect of engagement on score improvements, similar results were found.",
    "For the control group, the Multiple R was 0.873 with an R-Square value of 76.2%, indicating a strong correlation between engagement and score improvement."
  ],
